    "reasoning": "To implement the required finite-state machine (FSM) for the timer control, we need to define states that represent different stages of operation: searching for the start pattern (1101), shifting in 4 more bits, waiting for counting completion, and waiting for acknowledgment. We use localparam to define the states. The FSM uses the data input to detect the start pattern. When detected, it enables shift_ena for 4 cycles to shift in the duration data. Then it sets counting high while waiting for done_counting. After done_counting is high, it sets done high and waits for ack. The reset is synchronous and active high. A register is used for state storage and next_state logic is computed using combinational always block. Sequential logic follows standard Verilog style using posedge clk for state transitions.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input reset,\n    input data,\n    input done_counting,\n    input ack,\n    output reg shift_ena,\n    output reg counting,\n    output reg done\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam ST_SEARCH      = 3'd0;\n    localparam ST_SHIFT       = 3'd1;\n    localparam ST_WAIT_COUNT  = 3'd2;\n    localparam ST_DONE        = 3'd3;\n    localparam ST_ACK         = 3'd4;\n\n    // State register\n    logic [2:0] state;\n    logic [2:0] state_next;\n\n    // Internal signals\n    logic [3:0] shift_reg;\n    logic pattern_detected;\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            ST_SEARCH: begin\n                if (pattern_detected)\n                    state_next = ST_SHIFT;\n                else\n                    state_next = ST_SEARCH;\n            end\n            ST_SHIFT: begin\n                if (shift_reg[3] == 1'b1)\n                    state_next = ST_WAIT_COUNT;\n                else\n                    state_next = ST_SHIFT;\n            end\n            ST_WAIT_COUNT: begin\n                if (done_counting)\n                    state_next = ST_DONE;\n                else\n                    state_next = ST_WAIT_COUNT;\n            end\n            ST_DONE: begin\n                if (ack)\n                    state_next = ST_SEARCH;\n                else\n                    state_next = ST_DONE;\n            end\n            ST_ACK: begin\n                if (ack)\n                    state_next = ST_SEARCH;\n                else\n                    state_next = ST_ACK;\n            end\n            default: state_next = ST_SEARCH;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset)\n            state <= ST_SEARCH;\n        else\n            state <= state_next;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for outputs\n    always @(*) begin\n        shift_ena = 1'b0;\n        counting = 1'b0;\n        done = 1'b0;\n\n        case (state)\n            ST_SEARCH:;\n            ST_SHIFT: shift_ena = 1'b1;\n            ST_WAIT_COUNT: counting = 1'b1;\n            ST_DONE: done = 1'b1;\n            ST_ACK: done = 1'b1;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Shift register logic\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset) begin\n            shift_reg <= 4'b0000;\n        end else begin\n            case (state)\n                ST_SHIFT: begin\n                    shift_reg <= {shift_reg[2:0], data};\n                end\n                default:;\n            endcase\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Pattern detection logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        pattern_detected = 1'b0;\n        if (state == ST_SEARCH && shift_reg == 4'b1101)\n            pattern_detected = 1'b1;\n    end\n\nendmodule"
